Comment: My cousin did the same thing 20 years ago. She flew in Salvador with her then-husband to adopt a little girl. Once they were there, she was told it was sad to separate the child from her siblings (they didn't even know the little girl had a sister and a brother).  After months of administrative hell, 45 000$ of adoption fees and a total of 4 trips out there, they finally came back with 3 children. Back then, they were 2, 5 and 8.  It was not as hard as they expected regarding the adaptation but when they reached puberty, things got ugly. Only one of them in doing ok now, the other ones are not even talking to there (adoptive) parents... It is NOT a success story although my cousin and her husband are very good people, it seems like their best was not enough for these traumatized children... :(
